Some of you may have heard of bitcoin as a currency,

52
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:07,820
as a system of money that is currently 
wildly high in price one day and low the next.

53
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:16,140
I am here to tell you to ignore the price, ignore bitcoin
the money, but understand Bitcoin the technology...

54
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:19,260
and the network it creates.

55
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:24,260
If we mess up the money,
we can just reboot another currency.

56
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:34,200
Bitcoin the technology cannot be uninvented.
It creates the possibility for decentralized organization...

57
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:39,720
on a scale never seen before on this planet.

58
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:49,880
Here is why it's important to me: today in the world,
approximately one billion people have banking,

59
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:57,920
access to credit and international finance capabilities,
primarily among the upper classes and western nations.

60
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:04,180
Six and a half billion people on this planet 
have no connection to the world of [banking].

61
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:11,700
They operate in cash based societies with 
very little access to any international resources.

62
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:21,720
But they don't need banks. Two billion people are already
on the internet; with a simple application download,

63
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:28,920
they can become participants in an international
economy, using an international currency that...

64
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:32,880
