or] no fees, and no government controls.

65
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:42,540
They can connect to a world of international,
peer-to-peer finance. Bitcoin is the money of the people.

66
00:07:42,540 --> 00:07:49,600
[It operates according to] mathematical rules
that everyone agrees on. No [centralized] control.

67
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:57,260
Bring six and a half billion people into productive society,
connecting them to the rest of the world,

68
00:07:57,260 --> 00:08:00,400
is truly revolutionary.

69
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:07,560
First, we will start by affecting the payment processors,
these enormous companies that make it...

70
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:13,380
more expensive to send money
the poorer the destination country is.

71
00:08:13,380 --> 00:08:17,780
This situation is exploitative and corrupt.

72
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:26,580
These organizations profit enormously for a function 
that can be done in bitcoin for [little or no fee].

73
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:35,560
As an adage of the internet once went, I just replaced
your entire industry with a hundred lines of Python.

74
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:40,400
That is exactly what we will do with Bitcoin.

75
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:48,960
How can you use bitcoin today? Simply 
speaking, bitcoin can operate as a currency.

76
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:51,920
You can think of it as buying a foreign currency.

77
00:08:51,920 --> 00:09:00,680
You can connect to an exchange over the web,
wire some euros, and use them to buy bitcoin...

78
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:03,480
