79
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:10,440
But that is not really the right way to do it. 
We are entrepreneurs, right? We want to disrupt.

80
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:17,340
The best way [to obtain bitcoin] is by 
finding a product or service you can offer...

81
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:19,880
that someone with bitcoin would want to buy.

82
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:23,580
Start by earning bitcoin.

83
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:32,740
If you want to start a business, there are 
two barriers to becoming a global business.

84
00:09:32,740 --> 00:09:40,140
The first barrier: it is difficult to transport 
products and services across borders.

85
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:48,380
With the internet, we solved that. We can now create
products and services to sell that are virtual.

86
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:54,680
We could sell and deliver anywhere in the 
world, but we still had one big problem.

87
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:58,880
How do we get paid?
Bitcoin solves that part.

88
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:06,120
It allows us to receive payments from 
anywhere in the world, near instantaneously.

89
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:16,880
The Bitcoin network allows any individual to send
an amount as small one hundred millionth of a bitcoin,

90
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:23,000
which in today's terms is
a very tiny amount of money.

91
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,240
You can't do that with traditional
money and payment systems.

92
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:33,060
Credit cards were made in the 1950s, 
certainly not made for an internet age.

93
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:35,820
Bitcoin is made for the internet age.

94
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:43,520
If you can send payments that are one hundredth
or thousandth of a euro, you can sell content...

95
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:46,300
with microtransactions.

96
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:55,240
You can collect tiny payments from millions of people
and then aggregate them to be worth something.

97
00:10:55,240 --> 00:11:05,880
On the same network where you can send one
thousandth of a euro, you can send one billion euros.

98
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:12,460
The fee could be exactly the same, because
it depends on the size of the transaction in kilobytes,

99
00:11:12,460 --> 00:11:15,500
not the [value of the money].

100
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:21,720
Let's look back at the internet, the lessons 
we learned, and why bitcoin is important.

101
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:26,120
One of the most important principles
on the internet is neutrality.

102
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:31,520
The internet doesn't distinguish between 
large organizations and small organizations.

103
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:36,960
It doesn't know the difference
between CNN and an Egyptian blogger.

104
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:46,380
It provides the opportunity for a blogger to speak to
the world with the same power of voice that CNN has.

105
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:52,840
Bitcoin is neutral to sender and recipient,
as well as to the value of a transaction.

106
00:11:52,840 --> 00:12:01,800
That means every citizen and user of 
Bitcoin has the ability to innovate in finance.

107
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:10,580
Instruments, payment systems, and currency,
with the same facilities that a bank has.

108
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:20,580
You can become Citibank.
That is truly revolutionary.

109
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:29,680
It [transforms] a hierarchical system of international
finance that achieved security by limiting access.

110
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:36,440
That is the method of "trust" on our payment systems.
You can't get in unless you are vetted.

111
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:44,920
Bitcoin turns that on its head, with a flat and
decentralized network where every node is equal.

112
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:51,640
The protocol is neutral to the transactions 
and pushes innovation to the edge of the network.

113
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:58,760
This creates the same phenomenon we saw
on the internet: innovation without permission.

114
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:04,800
You don't need to ask anyone for your 
application to be published on the internet.

115
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:11,280
You don't need to ask anyone to completely subvert
a new industry with your information technology.

116
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:18,660
On Bitcoin, you don't need to ask anyone to invent a
new financial instrument, payment system, or service.

117
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:25,300
You can just do it. You can just write the code.
You are now part of an international financial network.

118
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:30,540
You can run that code and come
in contact with millions of consumers.

119
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:40,620
Now, it is still early days. We don't yet have 
the polished interfaces. It is difficult to use.

120
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:53,120
[The media says] it is used by criminals,
but it is not easy to see who is using bitcoin.

121
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:56,140
I have heard all of those [accusations] before.

122
00:13:56,140 --> 00:14:05,800
When I was on the internet in 1991, it was "a den
of thieves," pornographers, pirates, and criminals.

123
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:13,640
But it didn't matter and it doesn't matter now,
because the same power of the technology,

124
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:21,440
used by a criminal to promote their criminal activities,
can be used by all the rest of us to do good,

125
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:25,620
to do incredible things all across the world.

126
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:35,340
There are more of us. Bitcoin creates an environment
that is ripe for innovation. It is not just a currency.

127
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:39,400
It is a technology, a network, and a currency.

128
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:47,440
I can tell you, I am very happy that bitcoin's price is
climbing. I own some bitcoins, and it feels kind of nice.

129
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:52,820
But I don't care about the price.
If Bitcoin crashed tomorrow morning,

130
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:56,500
the technology is still revolutionary.

131
00:14:56,500 --> 00:15:07,220
If a website or application fails,
the internet doesn't go away.

132
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:13,860
If you understand that Bitcoin is a technology, not just
a currency, you can truly grasp its the importance.

133
00:15:13,860 --> 00:15:21,700
Again, it is not just about us.
It is about the other six billion.

134
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:28,740
It is about bringing financial integration 
that the world has never seen before.

135
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:34,040
From our perspective, it is a great technology
we can use for disruptive Innovation.

136
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:37,260
We can build some interesting services.

137
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:47,040
If you are a Kenyan farmer raising money to buy seeds,
you can join in decentralized, peer-to-peer lending,

138
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:57,320
and reach out to lenders all across the globe.
This is not just a technology, it is life-changing.

139
00:15:57,320 --> 00:16:05,860
The impact Bitcoin will have on the vast majority of the
world which lives under repressive and corrupt regimes,

140
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:11,280
with central banks that impose 
hyperinflation of 30% or more per month.

141
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:17,200
It is more important to see how
Bitcoin can affect all of those people.

142
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:21,960
There are two billion people on the internet;
only one billion of them have bank accounts.

143
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:25,880
We can change that. It will not be easy.

144
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:30,480
Make no mistake about it, when you 
[introduce] a disruptive technology into...

145
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:36,940
the middle of the most powerful organizations
[and governments] on the planet, they won't like it.

146
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:40,100
Right now, we are still in the early stages.

147
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:48,540
To use a trite expression, "First they ignore us, then
they laugh at us, then they fight us, and then we win."

148
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:53,460
We are still at the laughing stage,
and that is quite all right.

149
00:16:53,460 --> 00:17:00,480
By the time they start fighting us, they will have
already lost. This technology will be global.

150
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:07,400
More than $2.5 billion dollars has come from Chinese
investors who discovered a counterbalance...

151
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:11,980
to world domination by the global
reserve currency of the U.S. dollar.

152
00:17:11,980 --> 00:17:18,540
There are about 180 currencies in the world,
but there is only one international currency.

153
00:17:18,540 --> 00:17:26,840
There are about 180 currencies controlled by central
banks and governments, but only one is mathematical.

154
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:31,200
That is bitcoin. We will build more of them.

155
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:36,460
Cryptographic currencies will be
a mainstay of our financial future.

156
00:17:36,460 --> 00:17:47,940
They will be part of the future of this planet.
They [can't be] uninvented, and it is as simple as that.

157
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:51,920
You cannot turn that omelet back into eggs.

158
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:58,020
There are already have more than
a hundred competing currencies.

159
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:03,920
This shows how quickly innovation has 
exploded beyond bitcoin the currency.

160
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:10,660
There are many alternative coins, altcoins as
they're known, that use the same basic technology:

161
00:18:10,660 --> 00:18:18,340
a decentralized consensus network and an asset ledger.

162
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:27,060
There [can be] other forms of currency that are
inflationary or deflationary, that use demurrage...

163
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:29,100
or negative interest rates.

164
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:35,980
Currencies that redistribute a proportion
of the income to charitable organisations.

165
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:42,600
We can invent new forms of
money and financial instruments.

166
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:46,480
Bitcoin is programmable money.

167
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:51,360
Once you have programmable money,
the possibilities are truly endless.

168
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:58,140
Many of the basic concepts in our current 
system depend on legal contracts.

169
00:18:58,140 --> 00:19:07,920
We can convert them into algorithmic contracts
that can be enforced on the Bitcoin network.

170
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:21,740
As I said before, there is no counterparty. If I choose to
send value to another part of the peer-to-peer network.

171
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:23,880
no one is in between.

172
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:31,260
if I invent a new form of money, I can deploy it
to the entire world and invite others to join me.

173
00:19:31,260 --> 00:19:40,320
If you see that Bitcoin has the [potential]
to not only introduce money for the internet...

174
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:49,740
Because it is the perfect money for
the internet: instant, safe, and free.

175
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:56,800
Yes, it is money for the internet, but it is also
so much more. Bitcoin is the internet of money.

176
00:19:56,800 --> 00:20:08,360
Currency is only the first application. If you grasp that,
you can look beyond the fad and the price volatility.

177
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:16,940
At its core, it is a revolutionary technology that will
change the world forever. Join me in this revolution.

178
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:26,800
Thank you. [Applause]

